Comes all the way from LA to Chicago to go to a conference for Pilipino Americans in the mid-West to come together and continue learning my Filipinoness 🇵🇭 “The more you learn about where your people come from the more you learn about yourself” - my soul sister Gretchan 🦋  For some of us our families immigrate from countries they love or because they have to and leave behind culture in order to sustain a living for children like me LIKE YOU. The more I️ learn the more I️ admire my mothers and my mother’s mothers  resilience (shoutout to all the Lola’s and Lolos). I️ honor my family my culture the people who fight for our recognition and existence and all my sisters and brothers out here in America chasing this “dream” in a cold world 🌎 -side note for those who may not know the guy at the end is @dtrix a famous Filipino dancer who I️ grew up watching when I️ was younger 🕺🏻 #BAYBAYIN #KayaReunion #blessed #fortheculture #PSAFACT #stayconnected #family #isangbaksak

“Its too easy to be wanted I want too be valued.” 📸: @therealjakedixon

Student Athletes Committed to Honor otherwise known as SACH acts as a liaison between the Honor Committee and the athletic community and we create an open and honest forum for discussion of Honor and how it relates to student athletes.  We also engage in monthly discussions about the Honor System with our teams and provide feedback questions and ideas to the Honor Committee. If you want to learn more about SACH or meet the Exec board (pictured above) come out to our next meeting on the fourth floor of Newcombe at 5pm. I look forward to seeing you there! 🏏🏃🏾#uva #honorcode #wahoowah #hoostogether #uvalax #uvatrackandfield
10.13.95 // Blessed to see another year!  P.C:@cayla.not.kayla 🎈🎉🎊🙌🏾🎊🎊🎉🎊#22 #libraseason♎️
Day in the District ‼️🔆

I am happy to announce along with @jade_briana and @miabarron I will be launching a television show called THE HOO encompassing all UVA track and field and cross country on both the men's and women's teams. Along with meeting the teams you will get a more indepth look into the lives of our coaching staff the day in the life of a student athlete and recaps and previews of meets throughout the year.  I want to thank @coachfetz along with Stephanie Whitley for all your support with getting the show started and I am extremely excited to see what happens going forward. I also want to thank the Virginia Sports Video Services Department for getting myself and @jade_briana ingrained in producing The HOO. Lastly thank you to all of my friends family and mentors in the broadcasting realm who have helped me and inspired me in a variety of different ways and have helped me with  the little details while being a resource for me to pick their brains and learn something new each and everyday. 📍📍🛑🛑Also: Please come out and support the @uvacrosscountry team as they compete at Panorama Farms at 10AM EST! 👈🏽 I look forward to seeing you all there!! GO HOOS #uvatrackandfield #uvacrosscountry #THEHOO #hoostogether

Do you have hesitations? Here are some of the things than ran through my mind before this trip. :::::: Am I too old for this? Going into this trip I honestly expected for everyone to be in their early 20s but I was surprised to see that everyone was closer to my age (29)😩. Most people attending Yacht week are between  26-32 and a lot of them return year after year making more friends each time. :::::: Are the trips a non stop drinking party? No I would say it depends on the destination you select. Croatia is the original and the largest with over 60 boats going out each week this is the party destination. But places like Greece and Mallorca are much smaller (we only had 16 boats) and focus more on exploring the Mediterranean and docking at ports to explore the island. Perfect for me as I don’t really drink! :::::: Can you go solo? Absolutely! We all boarded the yacht as total strangers and with it being such tight quarters by day 2 we had already learnt so much about each other. :::::: I made some incredible memories and even better friends and I can’t wait to experience it again! I’d love to sail the Greece islands! Who’s in? :::::: Video by the mega talented @alexandermeliss! FOLLOW HIM! He’s all about extreme adventure and he’s a @gopro ambassador 🙌🏼 :::::: Visit the link in my bio to book your experience and destination! #theyachtweek #mallorca #sailing #mediterranean

God is moving!! The past couple days have been incredible. It's a small world and there have been moments where God is the only one that could make these occurrences happen. Just on Tuesday Night our flight from Munich to Paris got cancelled we were able to talk with European customer service and get on the next flight just an hour later on standby. We landed safely in Paris and took a bus to the station nearest our Hostel. We ended up running into a 25 year old man named Carlos who was from Yukatan and he was as lost as we were in such a new city. His friend he was meeting in Paris was a day late and he didn't have a place to stay. He ended up coming with us to our Hostel which was full and the owner of the hostel allowed him to sleep on the floor in our room. All day the next day he came with us to the Eiffel Tower and we shared stories we laughed and we didn't care about the language barrier or our life circumstances. For that moment we were One. He left that night as family and left us with a saying  Mi Casa es tu Casa   My house is your house . Later that night a young man named Anurug got to the Hostel but it was full and he pleaded for a spot the owner allowed him. I just started talking to him in the lobby and we conversed and talked about traveling experiences. He was from Tanzania. He ended up being by himself in Paris and We invited him to come along with us the next day to the Palace of Versailles. It was a beautiful day and again we shared stories and culture. He invited us to Tanzania and will continue to be a friend for a life time. It is these moments that we put differences aside to just be as God calls us to be One.

It always throws me off a bit when we change the clocks back an hour but that’s nothing in comparison to having five hours of daylight when I visited Iceland in winter. What time do you think it is here: sunrise at 10am or sunset at 3pm?

Who’s going to Iceland this winter?! The days in winter are short but the natural beauty is like nothing else. • For those of you traveling to Iceland this winter I’ve included a blog post I wrote earlier this year with everything you need to know as you plan your trip. Link in bio! ❄️
Are we photobombing the volcano or is the volcano photobombing us? P.S. Isn’t it exciting when self-timer shots turn out well?🏔

Bracing for impact. 🌊 But I actually did make this face as I stared in horror at my laptop last night. My site was being redirected to another site (NOT mine) after I made a few changes earlier in the day. The thought that I lost my travel writing and stories from the past four years was devastating. Thankfully Laviwashere.com is back up and running but it made me realize how truly intangible and virtual the Internet is. If I don’t print these photos and stories will I still have them in 50 years?

It’s not quite the same as the autumns I experienced in NYC and Madrid but I’ll take it. Weekend drives on the Pacific Coast Highway always make me feel like I’m seeing the Pacific Ocean for the first time.
I don’t get to see this view very often since I live in the Mission District. Whenever I make my way up here it always reminds me that I kind of love living in San Francisco.

Cinder Cone Volcano is surrounded by lava beds aptly named “Fantastic Lava Beds” 😂 and these unique rainbow-colored hills. Look at those colorful hills! The view from the top of Cinder Cone had me in awe seeing so many different landscapes in one 360-degree view.

I hope you scroll through to understand the whole picture. Cinder Cone Volcano looked like a massive pile of gravel until we got to the top. With every slippery step on the steep gravel we felt like we weren’t getting closer to the top. We didn’t expect to find the bowl-shaped crater in the middle which was once it’s volcanic vent. And a perfect view of Lassen Peak the volcano we hiked a day earlier. I’ve seen these other-worldly landscapes in Central and South America but never expected to see them in Northern California!

If you could have a house on the beach or in the mountains which would you choose? . The beaches of San Francisco are too cold for me so I’ve taken to the mountains when I go on weekend trips nearby. I’m much more of a mountain gal than I used to be but I still think I’d choose the beach. But where? Hmm...I’m going to take my imaginary fortune and think this over some more...💸

Why do hot springs look so cool but smell so bad?! It’s the sulfur. It’s one of those things you know you shouldn’t touch but you’re still kind of tempted to. I resisted getting too close to the hot springs at Bumpass Hell in Lassen Volcanic National Park. All fingers intact 🤗

When I feel self-doubt creeping in I remember all the distant places I’ve been and adventures I’ve had many of them alone. I have more experiences and stories under my belt than I ever expected at age 29. Screw self-doubt. I could do this all over in a heartbeat.

I woke up Monday morning to the smell of fire smoke. I thought the neighbors had a barbecue the night before but it turns out the smoke in San Francisco was coming from fires in the #Napa Valley area and the North Bay. Working in the wine industry I drive past Napa’s vineyards at least once a week. I took for granted those long drives next to rolling vineyards not paying attention to the beauty surrounding me. I’m hoping for some good news soon and sending ❤️ to all those impacted by this devastation.

This was an experience I will never forget--catching the last light on top of the Swiss Alps. It was one of those moments I almost couldn't believe was real. Switzerland was hands down one of the most beautiful countries I've ever visited in my life. Thank you to @engelberg.titlis for making this experience possible 🏔💕#flyswissbacktonature

Is there anything more wonderful than watching the release of rehabilitated animals back into their natural habitat 😍💚 via the man himself @richardobarry ・・・ Today was a great day. We released four rehabilitated loggerhead turtles back into the sea. We were about 20 miles offshore in 1000 feet of water. These turtles demonstrate the need to create a sanctuary in the Gulf of Taranto. Turtles whales dolphins and everything else alive in the gulf is being negatively impacted by corporate greed. There’s a ship in the area blasting away with an air gun 27/7. They are looking for oil and gas deposits. More about this and the proposed sanctuary later. Meanwhile there’s a massive hurricane heading for Japan. My thoughts and prayers are with our Cove Monitor Cynthia Fernandez and our Japanese friends and colleagues. #greenrope #joniandolphinconservation #dolphinproject

Today is #worldmentalhealthday 1 in 5 Americans struggle with mental disorders each year and I am one of them. (*gasps* omg how could she share that on social media) Anxiety and depression can make life a whirlwind of confusion and emotional exhaustion. Somedays it makes you wake up and literally just say  NO.  It is absolutely nothing to be ashamed of you showed up today that counts. But for those of you who aren't around me on a daily basis or aren't more than acquaintances how would you know that I was dealing with anxiety regularly if I hadn't written this post? Exactly. Mental disorders occur in people of all colors shapes sizes religions political views ages and backgrounds. So let's end the stigma and start the conversations. No one should feel like they are experiencing the effects of mental disorders alone. Chances are there are a lot more people in your life than you might think who are dealing with these things on a day to day basis. So if there's anything you take away from this it's plz be kind to everyone you meet and always make taking good care of yourself a top priority!!! 🎉💕

We tend to fall into cyclic patterns of overthinking and self-criticizing that ruin our perception of life sometimes to the point of no longer wanting it. I've lost friends to suicide and almost lost many more the past few years. Suicide and suicide ideation are severe issues that often go unaddressed.  So let's go back to when we were little kids and we weren't afraid to ask for help when we needed it. Let's try to judge less both ourselves and others and breathe a little more deeply. Let go of the internship that you didn't get the test you bombed or the ass that didn't text you back.  Go ahead and scream cry punch a hole in the wall (security deposit tho) make pickle voodoo dolls like from Lilo & Stitch (personal fav) - whatever you need to do to get through it. Just don't hesitate to reach out. Don't ever give up on yourself. #WorldSuicidePreventionDay

4. Self. I sacrificed a lot for my dream of being a rocket scientist but as people around me earned summer jobs I was afraid. I feared I wasn't good enough and as I searched for something external to tell me I was I lost my identity. I started trying to fit the part:  What should I being doing?  Rather than  What do I want to do?  Recently a quote resonated with me: at the end of the day all we have is ourselves. No one can convince you of how amazing you are except yourself so take time for yourself do what you want and above all: love yourself. Your self expression might just put you the place you want to be. Trust me I'm a NASA engineer (intern). || Thank you to the people who have given me that advice for months: you were right but I wasn't ready to listen--you know who you are.

3. Brother. We weren't always good siblings but we figured it out. I couldn't be more thankful for the mutual respect we have for each other but I admire your respect of self. The best advice you ever gave me was simply  Do what you want.  At the end of the day you take life into your own hands make mistakes succeed fail but you always stay sure in yourself. Thank you for teaching me to love myself and above all: make my own luck. #nationalsiblingday

~prepare for long caption~  dear lone wolf  i know at the end of the night when the lights turn off and the shoes come off and the conversations wear down you wipe off the fake smiles like the eyeliner you pencil in every morning. you lie awake unblinkingly staring at the ceiling as if there was some kind of hidden message encrypted there that had all the answers to why you feel like you’re taking on the weight of the world with no one there beside you. some kind of easy formula an a squared plus b squared equals c squared kind of arrangement that would suddenly unravel all these thoughts that are taking over your brain.  i know it’s not that easy.  but tell me why when you reflect on every thing you said or did that you wish you hadn’t when you cringe at how you’ve acted and who you’ve unintentionally hurt…tell me why you forget to include those who have been by your side through it all.  i know it’s not that easy. but you need to remember that you are not as alone as you might think. you are not a single flicker of light; you are a flame in a fire of love and passion and happiness. you are not alone.  remember the kindness lurking in the shadows. the acquaintances who look forward to seeing your smile every morning so it can light up their day. the puppies who tug on their leashes when they see you because they must absolutely positively no doubt be close to you. remember the late night conversations the confessions the “i know i can trust you”s and “thank you for being here for me”s. remember that you have touched people like a ripple in a pond. remember that many lives wouldn't  be the same without you here.  people care. whether this information is obviously displayed or not people care. you are not alone.  you are beautiful. you are wonderful. you are loved. never forget that.  the next time you find yourself lying awake remember the silent gratitudes. the unsung heroes. you will get better. you will get to where you need to be. but for now just remember - you are somebody’s reason to be. so never stop being.  love sammy

Dawg Camp has introduced me to a part of myself I did not even know existed. My story at the University of Georgia started with Dawg Camp Adventure in the summer of 2014 and I am so happy to say it's been a part of my life since. The impact that my fellow staff members and campers have had on me is immeasurable. I find new ways to fall in love with this school every single year because of Dawg Camp! Fall in love with UGA all over again and experience the magic that is Dawg Camp. The app closes in a couple of hours so APPLY!!! dawgcamp.uga.edu

What does UGA mean to me?  Home. I moved to the Georgia about six years ago from Washington state halfway through my high school career. Although my new school was a wonderful place I found it difficult to fit in and truly be myself. So when I came to UGA I was looking for somewhere I could grow. Somewhere to find a community. Somewhere to call a home.  I have found that here at Georgia. I have been challenged intellectually and have had the blessing of being inspired by my peers. I am excited that I get to constantly enjoy what I have chosen to study. How lucky am I that my mind is blown every day I go to class! I have received such a rounded education here-I am confident in my abilities to contribute and give back to the communities that have given so much to me.  In the end the organization endorsements don't matter. The campaigning the stickers the buttons the profile pictures all of those are temporary. They will fade with time. However the endless amount of support and love that I have felt is not. No matter the outcome of this week I will always remember this feeling. And no matter who is crowned I know that they will be absolutely deserving because this Court is full of incredible individuals who will all change the world in their own ways! And we all owe it to the University of Georgia. What an honor. Vote for who you truly believe deserves this! https://uga.campuslabs.com/engage/
